cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.IR

The paper proposes a convolutional neural network-based solution for arithmetic encoding in lossless image compression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) as image compression is a common application in computer vision. The paper also involves probability prediction and modeling, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves data compression, which can be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
